  "title": "Multi-index search of the same index prevents routing from working",
  "body": "## 🐛 Bug description\r\n\r\nUsing multi-index search prevents routing from updating the URL when searching on the same index.\r\n\r\n## 🔍 Bug reproduction\r\n\r\n1. Go to https://codesandbox.io/s/github/algolia/doc-code-samples/tree/isjs-v4/InstantSearch.js/multi-index-hits?file=/src/app.js\r\n2. Change the second index to \"instant_search\"\r\n3. Add routing to the search\r\n4. Type and search term and the URL does not update\r\n\r\n<!-- A live example helps a lot! Fork the sandbox, reproduce the bug and paste the URL here: -->\r\n\r\n**Live reproduction:**\r\n\r\nhttps://codesandbox.io/s/multi-index-hits-forked-xeby6\r\n\r\n## 💭 Expected behavior\r\n\r\nExpect the URL to be updated with the search term.",
